(2 : ‚ĄĚ) * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ) + Real.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ)) < (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ) ^ 2 + 1 := by\n              nlinarith [sq_nonneg ((2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ) - 2)]\n            exact h‚āĀ‚āĄ\n          -- Now we need to show that p > 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) + ‚ąö(2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1))\n          -- Since p is a prime divisor of (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) ^ 2 + 1, and (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) ^ 2 + 1 > 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) + ‚ąö(2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1)),\n          -- we can use the fact that p is at least the smallest prime divisor of (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) ^ 2 + 1, which is greater than 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) + ‚ąö(2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1)).\n          -- This is a bit involved, so we use a simpler approach: if p ‚Č§ 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) + ‚ąö(2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1)), then p would divide (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) ^ 2 + 1 - p * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1),\n          -- which is less than p, leading to a contradiction.\n          -- However, this approach is not straightforward, so we instead note that for N ‚Č• 1,\n          -- (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) ^ 2 + 1 > (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) + ‚ąö(2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1)))^2,\n          -- which implies that any prime divisor p of (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) ^ 2 + 1 must be greater than 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) + ‚ąö(2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1)).\n          -- For N = 0, we need to check manually.\n          have h‚āĀ‚āĄ : (p : ‚ĄĚ) > 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ) + Real.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ)) := by\n            by_contra h‚āĀ‚āÖ\n            have h‚āĀ‚āÜ : (p : ‚ĄĚ) ‚Č§ 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ) + Real.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ)) := by linarith\n            have h‚āĀ‚āá : (p : ‚Ąē) ‚Č§ 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) + ‚ĆäReal.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ))‚Ćč := by\n              have h‚āĀ‚āą : (p : ‚ĄĚ) ‚Č§ 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ) + Real.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ)) := h‚āĀ‚āÜ\n              have h‚āĀ‚āČ : (p : ‚ĄĚ) ‚Č§ 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ) + Real.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ)) := h‚āĀ‚āÜ\n              have h‚āā‚āÄ : (p : ‚Ąē) ‚Č§ 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) + ‚ĆäReal.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ))‚Ćč := by\n                have h‚āā‚āĀ : (p : ‚ĄĚ) ‚Č§ 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ) + Real.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ)) := h‚āĀ‚āÜ\n                have h‚āā‚āā : (‚ĆäReal.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ))‚Ćč : ‚ĄĚ) ‚Č§ Real.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ)) := by\n                  exact Int.floor_le (Real.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ)))\n                have h‚āā‚āÉ : (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ) + ‚ĆäReal.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ))‚Ćč : ‚ĄĚ) ‚Č§ 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ) + Real.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ)) := by\n                  linarith\n                have h‚āā‚āĄ : (p : ‚ĄĚ) ‚Č§ 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ) + Real.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ)) := h‚āĀ‚āÜ\n                have h‚āā‚āÖ : (p : ‚Ąē) ‚Č§ 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) + ‚ĆäReal.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ))‚Ćč := by\n                  by_contra h‚āā‚āÜ\n                  have h‚āā‚āá : (p : ‚Ąē) > 2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) + ‚ĆäReal.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ))‚Ćč := by linarith\n                  have h‚āā‚āą : (p : ‚ĄĚ) > (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) + ‚ĆäReal.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ))‚Ćč : ‚ĄĚ) := by\n                    norm_cast\n                  have h‚āā‚āČ : (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1) + ‚ĆäReal.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ))‚Ćč : ‚ĄĚ) ‚Č• (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ) + ‚ĆäReal.sqrt (2 * (2 * N ^ 2 + 1 : ‚ĄĚ))‚Ćč :",
      "choosing `n = 4m¬≤` is too weak. Instead, try something else. \n\n**Observation:**\nLet‚Äôs try choosing `n = 4k` (a multiple of 4). \n\n```\nn¬≤ + 1 = 16k¬≤ + 1. \n```\n\nIf `p` divides `16k¬≤ + 1`, then `16k¬≤ ‚Č° -1 mod p`, so `(4k)¬≤ ‚Č° -1 mod p`, and `(4k)^4 ‚Č° 1 mod p`. \nThus the multiplicative order of `4k` is `4`, hence 4 divides `p - 1`, so `p ‚Č° 1 mod 4`.\n\nSuppose that `p ‚Č§ 4k + 1`. \n\nThen `(4k)^2 ‚Č° -1 mod p`, and since `4k < p` (if `p ‚Č§ 4k + 1` and `p ‚Č• 17`, as below), then `(4k)^2 < p¬≤`, so `(4k)^2 = kp - 1`. \nThus `16k¬≤ = kp - 1`. \n\nBut `p ‚Č§ 4k + 1`, so `kp - 1 ‚Č§ k(4k + 1) - 1 = 4k¬≤ + k - 1 < 16k¬≤` for `k ‚Č• 1`.\n\nBut let‚Äôs assume for contradiction that `p ‚Č§ 4k`. Then `p ‚Č§ 4k`, and since `(4k)¬≤ ‚Č° -1 mod p`, then `p` divides `(4k)¬≤ + 1 = 16k¬≤ + 1`, so `p ‚Č§ 4k`, but `16k¬≤ + 1 < (4k)^2 + (4k)^2 = 32k¬≤` unless `k = 0`.\n\nHmm, no. \n\nAlternatively, `p ‚Č§ 4k`, and `p` divides `16k¬≤ + 1`. \n\nBut if `p ‚Č§ 4k`, then `p` divides `16k¬≤ + 1`, but `p` also divides `(4k)¬≤ = 16k¬≤`, so `p` divides `(16k¬≤ + 1) - 16k¬≤ = 1`, hence `p = 1`, a contradiction unless `k = 0`.\n\nThus if `p` divides `16k¬≤ + 1` and `p ‚Č§ 4k`, then `p = 1`, impossible. \n\nThus if `p` divides `n¬≤ + 1` and `n = 4k`, `p > 4k`. \n\nNow check `p` vs `2n + sqrt(2n)`:\n\n`p > 4k`, and `2n + sqrt(2n) = 8k + sqrt(8k) < 8k + 3‚ąök` (since `sqrt(8k) < 3‚ąök` for `k ‚Č• 3`).\n\nBut for `p > 4k`, we have `p` could be `4k + 1` (e.g., for `k = 1`, `n = 4`, `n¬≤ + 1 = 17`, `p = 17`). Then `4k + 1 = 5`, `2n + sqrt(2n) ‚Čą 10.8`, but `p = 17 > 10.8`.\n\nThus it seems that choosing `n = 4k`:\n\nIf",
      "\n  intro N\n  have h_main : ‚ąÉ n : ‚Ąē, n ‚Č• N ‚ąß ‚ąÉ p : ‚Ąē, Nat.Prime p ‚ąß p ‚ą£ n ^ 2 + 1 ‚ąß (p : ‚ĄĚ) > 2 * n + ‚ąö(2 * n) := by\n    -- Use a sufficiently large n of the form (k^2 + 1)\n    use max N (2 ^ (2 * N + 1))\n    constructor\n    ¬∑ -- Prove that n ‚Č• N\n      exact le_max_left N (2 ^ (2 * N + 1))\n    ¬∑ -- Find a prime p dividing n¬≤ + 1 and satisfying p > 2n + sqrt(2n)\n      have h‚āĀ : ‚ąÉ p : ‚Ąē, Nat.Prime p ‚ąß p ‚ą£ (max N (2 ^ (2 * N + 1)) : ‚Ąē) ^ 2 + 1 ‚ąß (p : ‚ĄĚ) > 2 * (max N (2 ^ (2 * N + 1)) : ‚Ąē) + ‚ąö(2 * (max N (2 ^ (2 * N + 1)) : ‚Ąē)) := by\n        -- Use the fact that n¬≤ + 1 has a prime divisor greater than 2n + sqrt(2n) for large n\n        have h‚āā : (max N (2 ^ (2 * N + 1)) : ‚Ąē) ‚Č• 2 ^ (2 * N + 1) := by\n          exact le_max_right _ _\n        have h‚āÉ : (max N (2 ^ (2 * N + 1)) : ‚Ąē) ‚Č• N := by\n          exact le_max_left _ _\n        -- Use n = 2^(2N+1)\n        have h‚āĄ : ‚ąÉ p : ‚Ąē, Nat.Prime p ‚ąß p ‚ą£ (2 ^ (2 * N + 1)) ^ 2 + 1 ‚ąß (p : ‚ĄĚ) > 2 * (2 ^ (2 * N + 1)) + ‚ąö(2 * (2 ^ (2 * N + 1))) := by\n          -- Use the fact that n¬≤ + 1 has a prime divisor greater than 2n + sqrt(2n)\n          have h‚āÖ : ‚ąÄ k : ‚Ąē, ‚ąÉ p : ‚Ąē, Nat.Prime p ‚ąß p ‚ą£ (2 ^ (2 * k + 1)) ^ 2 + 1 ‚ąß (p : ‚ĄĚ) > 2 * (2 ^ (2 * k + 1)) + ‚ąö(2 * (2 ^ (2 * k + 1))) := by\n            intro k\n            -- Use the fact that (2^(2k+1))¬≤ + 1 = 4^(2k+1) + 1 and find a prime divisor\n            have h‚āÜ : (2 : ‚Ąē) ^ (2 * k + 1) > 0 := by positivity\n            have h‚āá : (2 : ‚Ąē) ^ (2 * k + 1) ‚Č• 1 := by\n              apply Nat.one_le_pow\n              <;> norm_num\n            -- Use the fact that 4^(2k+1) + 1 has a prime divisor of the form 8k + 1\n            have h‚āą : ‚ąÉ p : ‚Ąē, Nat.Prime p ‚ąß p ‚ą£ (2 ^ (2 * k + 1)) ^ 2 + 1 ‚ąß (p : ‚ĄĚ) > 2 * (2 ^ (2 * k + 1)) + ‚ąö(2 * (2 ^ (2 * k + 1))) := by\n              -- Use the fact that (2^(2k+1))¬≤ + 1 = 4^(2k+1) + 1 and find a prime divisor\n     